Reasoning: The paper introduces a dataset and implementation of a first-person shooter game for training and evaluating computer vision methods such as object recognition, detection, segmentation, tracking, ego-motion estimation, monocular depth estimation, and scene segmentation. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category, with potential applications in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the game implementation and dataset could be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
